h</i> is the name of the husband of the Virgin Mary. It is also borne by a rich Jew, Joseph of Arimathea (Matthew 27:57; Mark 15:43; Luke 23:50; John 19:38), who took Jesus down from the Cross, wrapped him in a shroud, and buried him in a rock tomb. According to medieval legend, Joseph of Arimathea brought the Holy Grail to Britain. The name was uncommon in Britain in the Middle Ages but was revived in the mid 16th century and had become popular by the 1630s, remaining so ever since."],"variants":[{"name":"Josef","meanings":[", Dutch, Scandinavian, and Czech spelling of   Joseph  , now also in use in the English‐speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joseph Balbirny was born in 1400, in Markinch, Fife, Scotland as the son of Josoph Balbirny. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in 1455, in Scotland, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1400–1455":"1400–1455","1420–1440":"1420–1440","1375–1424":"1375–1424","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","Scotland":"Scotland","Markinch, Fife, Scotland":"Markinch, Fife, Scotland"},"fi":{"1400–1455":"1400–1455","1420–1440":"1420–1440","1375–1424":"1375–1424","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","Scotland":"Scotland","Markinch, Fife, Scotland":"Markinch, Fife, Scotland"},"fr":{"1400–1455":"1400–1455","1420–1440":"1420–1440","1375–1424":"1375–1424","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","Scotland":"Écosse","Markinch, Fife, Scotland":"Markinch, Fife, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Joseph Balbirny est né en 1400, à Markinch, Fife, Écosse, fils de Josoph Balbirny. Il a eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1455, à Écosse, à l’âge de 55 ans."},"de":{"1400–1455":"1400–1455","1420–1440":"1420–1440","1375–1424":"1375–1424","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","Scotland":"Scotland","Markinch, Fife, Scotland":"Markinch, Fife, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Joseph Balbirny wurde 1400 in